==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Articulated
<hw>Ar*tic"u*la`ted</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>United by, or provided with, articulations; jointed; <as>as, an
<ex>articulated</ex> skeleton</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Produced, as a letter, syllable, or word, by the
organs of speech; pronounced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Articulately</ent>⟦br⟧
